WEBVTT

00:00:13.105 --> 00:00:15.585
{\an8}I realized I can't live without you.

00:00:16.785 --> 00:00:18.545
{\an8}This is Yanin.
The ex-girlfriend I told you about.

00:00:19.385 --> 00:00:21.385
{\an8}This is Sailom. My boyfriend.

00:00:21.465 --> 00:00:25.345
{\an8}And today… I’ve made a choice of my own.

00:00:25.425 --> 00:00:28.185
{\an8}But I’m here to ask for your help.

00:00:28.265 --> 00:00:30.625
{\an8}Can you please help your sister?

00:00:30.705 --> 00:00:31.905
{\an8}What’s wrong with her?

00:00:31.985 --> 00:00:33.745
{\an8}She has Aplastic Anemia.

00:00:33.825 --> 00:00:35.905
{\an8}She needs a bone marrow transplant.

00:00:35.985 --> 00:00:37.425
{\an8}I’ve made my decision.

00:00:37.505 --> 00:00:38.545
{\an8}I’m going to help her.

00:00:38.625 --> 00:00:40.585
{\an8}I’m so proud of you, Pi Doc.

00:02:04.345 --> 00:02:05.305
Mom.

00:02:06.465 --> 00:02:07.625
Mom.

00:02:07.705 --> 00:02:08.864
Nabnueng.

00:02:11.665 --> 00:02:12.785
What is it, dear?

00:02:13.425 --> 00:02:14.545
I’m thirsty.

00:02:14.625 --> 00:02:15.865
Of course.

00:02:25.625 --> 00:02:26.465
Does your back hurt?

00:02:27.065 --> 00:02:28.345
Should I call the doctor?

00:02:28.945 --> 00:02:30.025
It's okay, Mom.

00:02:30.105 --> 00:02:31.025
I…

00:02:31.105 --> 00:02:33.665
It's just a bit stiff. I'll be fine soon.

00:02:33.745 --> 00:02:34.745
Are you sure?

00:02:34.825 --> 00:02:35.865
Yes.

00:02:36.385 --> 00:02:37.585
Take it slow.

00:02:42.545 --> 00:02:47.105
And if it hurts,
you must tell me immediately.

00:02:47.185 --> 00:02:49.745
Yes, Mom. Thank you.

00:02:50.825 --> 00:02:53.705
-Want some more?
-I’m fine now. Thank you.

00:03:06.785 --> 00:03:07.625
Lada.

00:03:07.705 --> 00:03:08.865
Lada.

00:03:08.945 --> 00:03:10.345
Come to visit Nabnueng?

00:03:11.865 --> 00:03:12.865
Yes.

00:03:32.985 --> 00:03:34.065
Nabnueng,

00:03:35.505 --> 00:03:38.305
thank you so much for saving your sister.

00:03:38.385 --> 00:03:39.705
It's nothing.

00:03:41.305 --> 00:03:42.345
I'm a doctor.

00:03:43.385 --> 00:03:44.905
Helping people is what I do.

00:03:47.025 --> 00:03:49.465
How is Nene?

00:03:49.545 --> 00:03:54.505
The doctor said
the transplant is finished.

00:03:55.145 --> 00:03:58.465
She’s in the sterile room now,

00:03:58.545 --> 00:04:01.625
waiting for the new
blood cells to start working.

00:04:01.705 --> 00:04:04.065
Then, please tell Nene that…

00:04:04.865 --> 00:04:06.745
PI Doctor Nabnueng will
come to visit her soon.

00:04:07.665 --> 00:04:08.825
Of course.

00:04:09.745 --> 00:04:10.665
Nabnueng,

00:04:11.585 --> 00:04:15.705
you can visit Nene at home if you want.

00:04:24.425 --> 00:04:26.465
Pi Nabnueng!

00:04:26.545 --> 00:04:28.585
How are you feeling?

00:04:30.265 --> 00:04:31.585
It doesn't hurt at all.

00:04:33.905 --> 00:04:35.665
Hello, Mrs. Lada.

00:04:36.745 --> 00:04:38.265
Hello.

00:04:38.345 --> 00:04:39.505
Hello there.

00:04:40.545 --> 00:04:42.625
Why did you bring all this stuff?

00:04:42.705 --> 00:04:43.945
Rations.

00:04:44.745 --> 00:04:46.305
It's just a little something.

00:04:46.945 --> 00:04:50.105
I was afraid you’d have nothing to eat,

00:04:50.185 --> 00:04:52.345
so I bought out the whole shop!

00:04:52.425 --> 00:04:54.905
Really? All of these
look like your favorites.

00:04:55.505 --> 00:04:58.745
No, they're yours. And these are…

00:04:58.825 --> 00:04:59.825
pistachio-filled!

00:05:02.505 --> 00:05:04.945
Love is in the air. Look at him,

00:05:05.025 --> 00:05:07.425
looking all handsome like a movie star.

00:05:07.505 --> 00:05:08.705
You're ready to go home.

00:05:08.785 --> 00:05:10.825
Am I supposed to look like a mess?

00:05:10.905 --> 00:05:12.705
You should!

00:05:12.785 --> 00:05:14.665
Are you hurt, Pi Doc?

00:05:14.745 --> 00:05:15.705
It hurts like hell.

00:05:15.785 --> 00:05:17.705
Such a shame. He's only 40--

00:05:17.785 --> 00:05:19.985
Hey, I’m not dead yet!

00:05:21.265 --> 00:05:22.585
So, does it hurt?

00:05:29.785 --> 00:05:32.025
Lada.

00:05:35.345 --> 00:05:39.265
Don’t you want to stay and
talk with your son a bit longer?

00:05:41.225 --> 00:05:45.185
I'll check on Nene. I don’t want
to leave her alone for too long.

00:05:46.705 --> 00:05:48.905
Whenever you want to see Nabnueng,

00:05:49.785 --> 00:05:51.705
you're always welcome.

00:05:55.785 --> 00:06:00.825
I'm not surprised at all that Nabnueng
turned out to be such a good man.

00:06:02.545 --> 00:06:04.865
I honestly don't know

00:06:04.945 --> 00:06:10.505
if he would have been this wonderful
if I had raised him myself.

00:06:13.305 --> 00:06:14.465
Phailin…

00:06:20.665 --> 00:06:22.225
Thank you so much

00:06:23.505 --> 00:06:25.625
for raising him so well.

00:06:43.145 --> 00:06:44.825
Please keep taking care of our son.

00:07:06.425 --> 00:07:07.745
-Sky
-Yes?

00:07:07.825 --> 00:07:08.905
What if…

00:07:09.705 --> 00:07:11.865
the surgery didn't work?

00:07:11.945 --> 00:07:15.305
What… if the cancer cells are still there?

00:07:15.385 --> 00:07:17.545
Don't think like that.

00:07:23.145 --> 00:07:24.225
Good day.

00:07:34.705 --> 00:07:38.305
Mr. Nava. Are you still feeling
any pain at the surgical site today?

00:07:38.385 --> 00:07:41.145
Well… it's still a bit sore.

00:07:42.425 --> 00:07:43.625
A dull, heavy kind of pain.

00:07:43.705 --> 00:07:44.825
I see.

00:07:44.905 --> 00:07:46.665
Nothing to worry about.

00:07:46.745 --> 00:07:49.305
You’ll be able to go home
and recover in just a few days.

00:07:49.385 --> 00:07:54.065
Is… there a chance
the cancer might come back?

00:07:54.145 --> 00:07:57.905
We've successfully removed
the tumor via laparoscopy.

00:07:57.985 --> 00:08:02.305
Next, we'll proceed with radiation therapy
to ensure all remaining cells are gone.

00:08:02.825 --> 00:08:04.945
You can rest easy.

00:08:05.025 --> 00:08:07.825
If we follow the plan,
he will definitely recover.

00:08:08.705 --> 00:08:13.745
Whether it returns depends on
his lifestyle choices from now on.

00:08:14.905 --> 00:08:15.945
Thank you, Doctor.

00:08:16.025 --> 00:08:18.665
You’re very welcome.
It’s my duty, after all.

00:08:18.745 --> 00:08:19.985
Please excuse me.

00:08:20.065 --> 00:08:21.425
Thank you so much.

00:08:28.865 --> 00:08:30.265
See?

00:08:31.225 --> 00:08:34.105
I told you it’s treatable.

00:08:36.945 --> 00:08:41.705
Thank you, Sky. For giving me
the courage to get treated.

00:08:43.144 --> 00:08:44.345
Don't mention it.

00:08:44.905 --> 00:08:47.865
We're… boyfriends now,

00:08:49.665 --> 00:08:50.785
right?

00:08:52.105 --> 00:08:53.185
Want some water?

00:08:53.265 --> 00:08:54.385
Water?

00:08:55.465 --> 00:08:56.305
Okay.

00:09:17.265 --> 00:09:19.625
Oh, you're home.

00:09:19.705 --> 00:09:22.065
I just finished cooking Sour Curry.

00:09:22.145 --> 00:09:24.105
Go wash your hands, and let's eat.

00:09:24.985 --> 00:09:26.265
Grandma,

00:09:27.225 --> 00:09:28.665
I have something to show you.

00:09:29.465 --> 00:09:30.425
What is it?

00:09:31.145 --> 00:09:32.105
Huh?

00:09:32.985 --> 00:09:34.145
Let me see.

00:09:46.425 --> 00:09:47.505
What…

00:09:49.025 --> 00:09:50.145
What kind of…

00:09:50.945 --> 00:09:52.265
contract is this?

00:09:53.545 --> 00:09:55.105
It’s a loan agreement.

00:09:56.865 --> 00:09:59.185
Madam Amy lent me
the money to redeem our house first.

00:10:00.545 --> 00:10:01.665
She said

00:10:02.425 --> 00:10:04.345
we can pay her back whenever we’re ready.

00:10:07.145 --> 00:10:08.185
Look.

00:10:09.865 --> 00:10:13.305
It says right here, zero interest.

00:10:14.905 --> 00:10:16.905
And she even let us keep
the title deed ourselves.

00:10:19.265 --> 00:10:21.505
Madam Amy is such a kind soul.

00:10:23.665 --> 00:10:24.985
Yes, she is.

00:10:32.865 --> 00:10:34.985
Now we can reopen our shop, Grandma.

00:11:10.345 --> 00:11:11.625
Good morning.

00:11:12.505 --> 00:11:14.305
Love Like a Bike at your service.

00:11:32.425 --> 00:11:37.705
One Americano.
Hot and no sugar, as requested.

00:11:39.545 --> 00:11:41.345
But I didn't order this.

00:11:43.465 --> 00:11:45.985
It's a special perk for being
Dr. Nabnueng's boyfriend.

00:11:49.865 --> 00:11:51.145
Thank you.

00:11:52.185 --> 00:11:53.985
Let's go inside.

00:12:04.705 --> 00:12:08.745
Don’t overthink this. I'm sure
Pi Doc is over his ex by now.

00:12:08.825 --> 00:12:10.905
I wouldn't be so sure.

00:12:10.985 --> 00:12:13.905
Some people still
can't let go of the old one.

00:12:14.945 --> 00:12:16.065
Sailom?

00:12:20.105 --> 00:12:21.185
Sailom.

00:12:23.465 --> 00:12:24.745
Sailom.

00:12:26.025 --> 00:12:27.065
Yes?

00:12:27.145 --> 00:12:29.105
Something on your mind?

00:12:38.425 --> 00:12:39.625
Pi Doc…

00:12:41.265 --> 00:12:46.105
when you called me
your boyfriend in front of your ex,

00:12:48.185 --> 00:12:50.025
did you really mean it?

00:12:50.105 --> 00:12:51.785
Or were you just trying to spite her?

00:12:52.705 --> 00:12:53.865
I mean…

00:12:53.945 --> 00:12:56.425
if you haven't moved on yet,

00:12:56.505 --> 00:12:57.825
I understand.

00:13:00.065 --> 00:13:03.825
Who could easily forget someone
they've been with for so long?

00:13:07.265 --> 00:13:08.825
It's okay.

00:13:08.905 --> 00:13:10.185
I can wait.

00:13:29.025 --> 00:13:30.185
Sailom,

00:13:32.585 --> 00:13:33.785
listen to me.

00:13:36.345 --> 00:13:38.945
What I felt for Yanin

00:13:39.905 --> 00:13:41.265
is over.

00:13:44.065 --> 00:13:47.185
You probably want to know
when it ended, right?

00:13:50.585 --> 00:13:52.065
Truth is,

00:13:53.225 --> 00:13:54.705
I don't even know.

00:13:56.505 --> 00:13:57.985
But what I do know

00:13:59.785 --> 00:14:01.705
is that I love my new boyfriend.

00:14:06.065 --> 00:14:08.225
The boyfriend who's sitting right here.

00:14:21.545 --> 00:14:22.665
Pi Doc!

00:14:32.025 --> 00:14:33.225
Want another one?

00:15:00.225 --> 00:15:03.585
{\an8}When Sky told me he wanted
to bring his boyfriend to stay with us,

00:15:03.665 --> 00:15:06.345
I was so curious.

00:15:06.425 --> 00:15:08.265
So it was you, Nava.

00:15:09.305 --> 00:15:10.425
I am.

00:15:10.505 --> 00:15:11.625
Sky,

00:15:12.265 --> 00:15:15.425
bringing your boyfriend home like this,
aren't you afraid we’ll find out that

00:15:15.505 --> 00:15:18.865
"Sky the Predator"
has turned into a "Little Kitty?"

00:15:19.785 --> 00:15:20.825
Tawan.

00:15:20.905 --> 00:15:22.025
{\an8}You're both gonna get it.

00:15:24.345 --> 00:15:26.265
Anyway, Mom. Like I said,

00:15:27.305 --> 00:15:29.185
Nava needs continuous radiation therapy.

00:15:29.265 --> 00:15:33.025
That's why I want him to
stay and recover here for a while.

00:15:33.105 --> 00:15:34.665
Are you okay with that?

00:15:35.705 --> 00:15:37.025
Of course, I am.

00:15:37.105 --> 00:15:40.185
I promise, as soon as I'm better,

00:15:40.265 --> 00:15:43.505
I'll find a job and move out.

00:15:44.185 --> 00:15:47.025
Don't go anywhere.
Since you're Sky’s boyfriend,

00:15:47.105 --> 00:15:48.345
you're like a son to me now.

00:15:49.265 --> 00:15:51.665
Just help me
keep this stubborn boy in line.

00:15:52.385 --> 00:15:54.065
Aww, Mom.

00:15:54.145 --> 00:15:56.185
I’m not that stubborn.

00:15:56.265 --> 00:15:57.705
Don’t tell Nava all that.

00:15:59.025 --> 00:16:01.825
Alright, take a seat.
I’ll come join you in a bit.

00:16:01.905 --> 00:16:04.065
Sky will take you
inside later this evening.

00:16:04.145 --> 00:16:05.665
-Thank you.
-Come.

00:16:05.745 --> 00:16:06.785
Come.

00:16:13.905 --> 00:16:14.985
Micky!

00:16:16.225 --> 00:16:17.305
Who delivered the deserts?

00:16:19.225 --> 00:16:22.185
Oh, PI Din…

00:16:23.425 --> 00:16:24.545
…sent them via a Rider.

00:16:35.825 --> 00:16:39.425
So, lately, when other people touch you,

00:16:39.505 --> 00:16:41.865
you don’t feel afraid anymore, right?

00:16:42.785 --> 00:16:43.865
Yes.

00:16:43.945 --> 00:16:46.305
As long as I'm aware of it,

00:16:46.385 --> 00:16:47.865
I don't feel anything.

00:16:48.545 --> 00:16:50.425
But I still get a bit

00:16:51.705 --> 00:16:55.105
startled if someone
touches me unexpectedly.

00:16:56.585 --> 00:17:00.825
The fact that you’re no
longer afraid of being touched

00:17:00.905 --> 00:17:04.505
is a huge step forward.

00:17:04.585 --> 00:17:07.105
I’m so proud of you, Mr. Sailom.

00:17:07.184 --> 00:17:11.944
And I want you to be proud of yourself.

00:17:12.025 --> 00:17:13.625
Keep believing in the process.

00:17:14.345 --> 00:17:17.704
If you continue with the treatment,

00:17:17.785 --> 00:17:20.865
I'm certain you will fully recover.

00:17:36.825 --> 00:17:38.185
How was your consultation?

00:17:39.385 --> 00:17:41.465
Why don't you ask your friend?

00:17:41.545 --> 00:17:43.145
You work in the same clinic.

00:17:44.105 --> 00:17:45.385
I can't do that.

00:17:46.665 --> 00:17:47.785
It’s medical ethics.

00:17:49.225 --> 00:17:51.425
Disclosing patient information
is strictly forbidden.

00:17:52.345 --> 00:17:55.745
Then… can a doctor
and a patient fall in love?

00:17:59.905 --> 00:18:01.425
Actually, they can't.

00:18:02.265 --> 00:18:03.305
Why not?

00:18:05.745 --> 00:18:07.025
Because therapy

00:18:07.665 --> 00:18:11.345
requires immense trust between
the psychiatrist and the patient.

00:18:11.425 --> 00:18:15.745
A doctor needs to see the most
vulnerable parts of a patient's heart

00:18:15.825 --> 00:18:17.065
for the treatment to work.

00:18:19.945 --> 00:18:21.505
If they were in love,

00:18:22.865 --> 00:18:27.745
the patient might be afraid to
open up about their inner struggles

00:18:29.065 --> 00:18:31.345
for fear of affecting the relationship.

00:18:32.425 --> 00:18:34.065
Then, the treatment fails.

00:18:35.585 --> 00:18:37.065
On the flip side,

00:18:38.025 --> 00:18:42.145
the doctor could be seen
as using that vulnerability

00:18:42.225 --> 00:18:45.185
to manipulate the patient's feelings.

00:18:45.785 --> 00:18:47.545
That's why it's forbidden.

00:18:50.585 --> 00:18:51.745
Then…

00:18:52.385 --> 00:18:54.945
you and I… we…

00:18:56.585 --> 00:18:58.385
I am a psychiatrist, that’s true.

00:18:59.385 --> 00:19:01.225
But you aren't my patient.

00:19:06.305 --> 00:19:07.665
Wait…

00:19:08.465 --> 00:19:10.945
so the reason you refused to
treat me from the start was…

00:19:21.185 --> 00:19:23.465
If you were my patient,

00:19:27.145 --> 00:19:29.025
we couldn't be boyfriends,

00:19:32.585 --> 00:19:33.665
right?

00:19:42.025 --> 00:19:43.265
I'm going home.

00:19:43.985 --> 00:19:45.505
Sailom.

00:19:45.585 --> 00:19:46.865
Need a ride?

00:19:47.785 --> 00:19:48.985
Sailom!

00:19:57.265 --> 00:19:59.505
Wait here for a bit.

00:19:59.585 --> 00:20:00.945
I'll go get you some water.

00:20:02.305 --> 00:20:03.425
Thank you.

00:20:17.665 --> 00:20:20.465
{\an8}PEDOPHILE DOCTOR ARRESTED
FOR MOLESTING A 14-YEAR-OLD BOY.

00:20:20.545 --> 00:20:22.745
{\an8}SHOCKING DISCOVERY
OVER 20 VICTIMS FOUND!

00:20:39.025 --> 00:20:40.105
Sailom.

00:20:41.185 --> 00:20:42.305
Okay…

00:20:47.345 --> 00:20:49.425
If you can hear my voice,
I’m right here with you.

00:20:53.225 --> 00:20:55.865
Take a deep breath in…

00:20:57.425 --> 00:20:59.585
and slowly breathe out.

00:21:08.265 --> 00:21:10.265
Where are you right now?

00:21:15.545 --> 00:21:17.545
I… I'm at home.

00:21:19.065 --> 00:21:20.745
I'm here with you, Pi Doc Nabnueng.

00:21:25.345 --> 00:21:27.585
How are you feeling?

00:21:36.785 --> 00:21:38.225
{\an8}He's my stepfather.

00:21:43.585 --> 00:21:45.345
Are you alright?

00:21:47.825 --> 00:21:49.065
I'm okay.

00:21:51.905 --> 00:21:53.065
I really am.

00:21:54.985 --> 00:21:56.425
Actually…

00:21:59.025 --> 00:22:03.385
I'm glad he's finally facing
the consequences of his actions.

00:22:05.785 --> 00:22:09.745
He won’t be able to hurt
any more unfortunate children.

00:23:01.505 --> 00:23:02.465
Din,

00:23:02.545 --> 00:23:05.265
do we still have a lot of
orders left for the bike shop?

00:23:06.225 --> 00:23:09.705
Uh… just the Éclair fillings, and

00:23:09.785 --> 00:23:11.425
two more trays of
Banana Cake and I'm done.

00:23:12.585 --> 00:23:15.265
After that, mix the dough
for Taro Bua Loy for me.

00:23:15.345 --> 00:23:17.865
-I’ve already steamed the taro for you.
-Will do.

00:23:18.665 --> 00:23:19.745
Oh,

00:23:19.825 --> 00:23:22.425
and did the duck farm deliver more eggs?

00:23:22.505 --> 00:23:26.385
Our Thong Yod and Foy Thong
are running low. I need to make more.

00:23:26.465 --> 00:23:29.265
I'll check that once the baking is done.

00:23:34.585 --> 00:23:37.865
And grate some coconuts for me too.

00:23:38.705 --> 00:23:39.825
Got it, Grandma.

00:24:11.945 --> 00:24:14.305
-What are you here for?
-Just checking on you.

00:24:18.865 --> 00:24:21.585
Ever since you quit and started
sending desserts to the shop instead,

00:24:21.665 --> 00:24:24.025
you haven't shown your face even once.

00:24:27.065 --> 00:24:30.065
I was worried we'd have
nothing to sell tomorrow, so I

00:24:30.145 --> 00:24:31.225
came to see for myself.

00:24:31.745 --> 00:24:33.865
Just say "I miss you" if you miss me.

00:24:34.505 --> 00:24:36.985
Miss you? In your dreams.

00:24:38.785 --> 00:24:43.065
Then go home. Your desserts will
definitely be ready by tomorrow.

00:24:45.945 --> 00:24:47.745
Fine, I missed you.

00:25:02.305 --> 00:25:03.425
Where are my snacks?

00:25:05.545 --> 00:25:09.305
In the oven. Almost done.

00:25:26.785 --> 00:25:28.905
Why haven't you
shown up at the cafe lately?

00:25:29.665 --> 00:25:30.665
Avoiding me?

00:25:31.825 --> 00:25:32.905
I'm not.

00:25:34.505 --> 00:25:36.945
I just reopened my shop a month ago.

00:25:37.025 --> 00:25:39.025
Things are still a bit messy.

00:25:42.065 --> 00:25:44.545
You’re really dedicated to this shop.

00:25:45.865 --> 00:25:47.065
Of course I am.

00:25:49.065 --> 00:25:51.105
I want this to succeed,

00:25:54.345 --> 00:25:56.065
so Grandma can finally have an easy life.

00:25:58.225 --> 00:26:00.025
Listen to you…

00:26:00.785 --> 00:26:01.985
talking like those

00:26:02.745 --> 00:26:04.625
"Young Billionaires."

00:26:06.225 --> 00:26:09.905
Well… everyone has
to think about their future.

00:26:11.425 --> 00:26:14.305
I'm glad to see you're
getting your life together.

00:26:16.265 --> 00:26:18.545
You don't have to go running
around taking so many jobs.

00:26:20.225 --> 00:26:21.545
Did you take the wrong medicine?

00:26:33.185 --> 00:26:34.305
What about you?

00:26:35.625 --> 00:26:40.465
How long do you plan
on being a bike mechanic?

00:26:43.505 --> 00:26:45.185
What is that supposed to mean?

00:26:52.585 --> 00:26:54.145
REMEMBER THIS TRAGEDY?
THE PLANE SKIDED, A YOUNG GIRL'S DEATH

00:26:56.105 --> 00:26:57.385
I think…

00:26:59.145 --> 00:27:00.465
if you went back to being a pilot,

00:27:03.105 --> 00:27:05.265
your future would go
much further than this.

00:27:07.985 --> 00:27:09.585
Stay the hell out of my business.

00:27:11.825 --> 00:27:12.825
Tawan.

00:27:13.465 --> 00:27:14.505
Tawan.

00:27:23.625 --> 00:27:24.665
Tawan.

00:27:25.345 --> 00:27:28.625
You’re not going back
because of that child?

00:27:29.465 --> 00:27:30.585
You bastard!

00:27:31.265 --> 00:27:33.345
I told you to stay out of it!

00:27:35.945 --> 00:27:36.945
So, that’s true.

00:27:38.025 --> 00:27:38.905
Goddamnit.

00:27:45.585 --> 00:27:48.505
If punching me makes
you feel better, go ahead.

00:27:57.425 --> 00:27:59.825
It was an accident.

00:28:00.425 --> 00:28:01.625
Nobody wanted it to happen.

00:28:02.265 --> 00:28:03.625
But I messed up!

00:28:05.905 --> 00:28:08.305
Because of me, Som had to die!

00:28:08.385 --> 00:28:10.585
How much longer are you
going to blame yourself?

00:28:11.785 --> 00:28:15.945
Have you ever thought about
how the people who love you feel?

00:28:21.145 --> 00:28:22.225
Listen to me.

00:28:24.545 --> 00:28:27.025
You can feel guilty for the
rest of your life if you want,

00:28:28.385 --> 00:28:29.785
because forgiving yourself

00:28:31.265 --> 00:28:32.985
is never easy.

00:28:34.185 --> 00:28:35.945
But don't just do it for yourself.

00:28:37.745 --> 00:28:38.945
Do it for Auntie Phailin,

00:28:39.705 --> 00:28:41.185
your family,

00:28:43.625 --> 00:28:44.785
the ones you love,

00:28:46.865 --> 00:28:48.345
and people who love you.

00:28:53.345 --> 00:28:55.065
Stop torturing yourself.

00:29:06.865 --> 00:29:07.945
Need a hug?

00:29:09.305 --> 00:29:10.465
My chest is free.

00:29:44.225 --> 00:29:46.425
I don't want to go back to the States.

00:29:48.305 --> 00:29:50.985
Can I just stay here
with you like this forever?

00:29:54.385 --> 00:29:56.185
You can't do that.

00:29:57.345 --> 00:29:59.225
You have to go back
and finish your studies, okay?

00:30:04.785 --> 00:30:06.145
It's so unfair.

00:30:07.265 --> 00:30:09.985
We’ve only just gotten close,

00:30:10.065 --> 00:30:11.625
and now I have to leave?

00:30:13.825 --> 00:30:17.105
I haven't had enough of
these moments with you yet.

00:30:20.105 --> 00:30:21.465
What kind of moments?

00:30:30.225 --> 00:30:31.585
Moments like this.

00:32:06.145 --> 00:32:07.985
One, two, go.

00:32:10.665 --> 00:32:11.825
Pi DinDin!

00:32:13.145 --> 00:32:14.345
Hello, Auntie Pailin.

00:32:14.425 --> 00:32:16.505
-Hey there, Lookso.
-Hello.

00:32:16.585 --> 00:32:18.625
What brings you here today?

00:32:18.705 --> 00:32:20.985
You usually
don't deliver the desserts yourself.

00:32:21.065 --> 00:32:23.665
I just… missed everyone at the café.

00:32:23.745 --> 00:32:27.145
Always the smooth talker, aren't you?

00:32:27.225 --> 00:32:31.105
Alright, I'll go transfer
the payment for the desserts.

00:32:31.185 --> 00:32:32.105
Thank you.

00:32:36.225 --> 00:32:37.065
Looking for someone?

00:32:38.785 --> 00:32:40.985
Oh… just looking around.

00:32:52.905 --> 00:32:54.705
Haven't seen you in days.

00:32:55.465 --> 00:32:57.745
I was about
to file a missing person's report.

00:32:58.865 --> 00:33:00.865
-Oh…
-Sky.

00:33:01.905 --> 00:33:04.585
Hey. Thought I was Tawan?

00:33:05.745 --> 00:33:07.905
So… where is he?

00:33:08.505 --> 00:33:10.185
Oh, Tawan told me

00:33:10.265 --> 00:33:12.065
he’s done with fixing bikes.

00:33:13.185 --> 00:33:15.585
Said he’s going to work in Bangkok,

00:33:17.025 --> 00:33:19.705
so I’m taking over for him.

00:33:21.065 --> 00:33:22.425
Bangkok?

00:33:22.505 --> 00:33:24.265
Didn't he talk to you about it?

00:33:25.385 --> 00:33:27.305
No, he didn't.

00:33:30.345 --> 00:33:32.145
And… uh…

00:33:33.145 --> 00:33:34.305
Hello.

00:33:35.465 --> 00:33:39.465
Oh, of course. You can come
to take your bicycle this evening.

00:33:40.385 --> 00:33:41.425
Yes.

00:33:45.105 --> 00:33:46.345
It's ready now.

00:33:47.105 --> 00:33:48.305
Yes.

00:33:49.145 --> 00:33:50.705
Ready now.

00:33:50.785 --> 00:33:51.785
Alright.

00:34:08.784 --> 00:34:12.665
Thank you so much for throwing
this farewell party for me.

00:34:13.264 --> 00:34:16.784
The food is amazing, and the
dipping sauce is so spicy.

00:34:19.585 --> 00:34:23.865
I’m going to miss your cooking
so much when I’m over there.

00:34:24.465 --> 00:34:25.784
Only missing the food?

00:34:25.865 --> 00:34:28.344
What about the "person?"

00:34:28.425 --> 00:34:29.425
He’s spicy too.

00:34:30.705 --> 00:34:32.225
Lookso.

00:34:33.865 --> 00:34:34.905
Sailom,

00:34:34.985 --> 00:34:36.465
Hurry up and graduate.

00:34:36.545 --> 00:34:38.505
Have some pity on the guy over there.

00:34:39.264 --> 00:34:44.425
Don't make him wait too long,
or he might just die from heartbreak.

00:34:55.945 --> 00:34:57.145
Pi Doc…

00:34:58.305 --> 00:34:59.705
don't worry about me.

00:35:00.625 --> 00:35:03.065
I'll study hard,
graduate as fast as I can,

00:35:03.745 --> 00:35:05.545
and come straight back to you.

00:35:10.185 --> 00:35:11.265
I know.

00:35:15.305 --> 00:35:17.185
Can I have one more
piece of grilled squid?

00:35:19.065 --> 00:35:22.065
You won't get to eat this
over there. Take ten pieces.

00:35:44.505 --> 00:35:46.785
I’m really gonna miss you so much.

00:35:48.305 --> 00:35:51.425
Don't be so dramatic.
He's going to study, not to war.

00:35:51.505 --> 00:35:52.745
Right, Sailom?

00:35:54.505 --> 00:35:55.425
Sailom?

00:35:58.345 --> 00:35:59.185
What's wrong?

00:36:02.305 --> 00:36:03.425
I'm scared.

00:36:06.385 --> 00:36:08.145
What are you afraid of?

00:36:08.225 --> 00:36:10.265
Worried Pi Doc will leave you?

00:36:12.945 --> 00:36:14.105
If it’s about that,

00:36:14.185 --> 00:36:16.665
you have nothing to fear.

00:36:16.745 --> 00:36:20.145
Besides, we can stay
connected all the time now.

00:36:20.225 --> 00:36:23.705
You can call him
whenever you miss him, right?

00:36:25.745 --> 00:36:26.705
I wouldn't be so sure.

00:36:27.345 --> 00:36:30.185
Even couples who’ve been
together for ages break up.

00:36:30.265 --> 00:36:32.105
They broke up before
he started dating our friend.

00:36:32.185 --> 00:36:35.585
No, what I'm saying is they
broke up because of the distance.

00:36:43.385 --> 00:36:47.585
But maybe you two will make it.

00:36:47.665 --> 00:36:48.585
Don't overthink it.

00:36:53.505 --> 00:36:54.945
Sailom. Where are you going?

00:36:55.025 --> 00:36:55.945
Sailom!

00:36:59.105 --> 00:37:00.305
I was trying to look out for him.

00:37:00.385 --> 00:37:01.945
Look out for him, my ass.

00:37:02.025 --> 00:37:03.545
What if he ends up getting hurt later?

00:37:25.345 --> 00:37:26.305
Pi Doc.

00:37:27.225 --> 00:37:28.385
Sailom?

00:37:29.705 --> 00:37:30.785
Is something wrong?

00:37:39.665 --> 00:37:41.625
You’re really going to wait for me, right?

00:37:43.185 --> 00:37:44.345
Of course, I'll wait.

00:37:46.425 --> 00:37:48.065
We won't end up…

00:37:49.505 --> 00:37:51.585
breaking up like you and your ex, will we?

00:38:02.785 --> 00:38:03.905
Sailom,

00:38:05.065 --> 00:38:06.745
Yanin and I ended

00:38:08.025 --> 00:38:10.825
because she left me
waiting without any goal.

00:38:11.625 --> 00:38:13.105
But with you,

00:38:13.945 --> 00:38:16.345
I'm certain it won't be like that.

00:38:18.585 --> 00:38:21.145
Seeing you rush here today

00:38:23.785 --> 00:38:25.345
only makes me confident

00:38:28.385 --> 00:38:30.985
that waiting for you is worth it.

00:38:35.585 --> 00:38:36.785
You said it.

00:38:37.465 --> 00:38:39.745
Now you have to promise me.

00:38:40.945 --> 00:38:44.985
While I’m gone, you aren’t
allowed to look at anyone else.

00:38:47.505 --> 00:38:49.105
Promise me.

00:38:50.905 --> 00:38:51.905
I promise.

00:38:52.985 --> 00:38:56.625
And you have to video call me every day.

00:38:58.465 --> 00:39:02.665
If you don't, I’ll fly back here
and deal with you myself!

00:39:07.225 --> 00:39:08.265
I will.

00:39:11.945 --> 00:39:12.865
Now, come here.

00:39:34.065 --> 00:39:35.465
I miss you so much.

00:39:36.225 --> 00:39:37.465
I miss you too.

00:39:40.465 --> 00:39:41.865
I really want to see you.

00:39:42.425 --> 00:39:43.945
I love you, Sailom.

00:39:47.225 --> 00:39:48.465
And how’s uni going?

00:39:50.105 --> 00:39:51.545
I'm so exhausted.

00:39:52.265 --> 00:39:53.785
I just want to whine to you so much.

00:39:54.585 --> 00:39:55.985
Go ahead.

00:39:56.585 --> 00:39:58.545
I'm so exhausted.

00:39:58.625 --> 00:40:00.945
I've been studying day and night.

00:40:01.025 --> 00:40:05.585
And I was late for class today because
I stayed up late reading last night.

00:40:06.145 --> 00:40:07.785
You know what?

00:40:10.985 --> 00:40:14.705
Sailom, the café is organizing
a cycling trip next month.

00:40:14.785 --> 00:40:18.305
It’s such a shame
you won’t be here to join us.

00:40:18.385 --> 00:40:19.665
I wish you were here.

00:40:23.545 --> 00:40:24.625
Sailom?

00:40:26.345 --> 00:40:27.465
Sailom!

00:40:37.705 --> 00:40:38.745
Goodnight.

00:41:01.105 --> 00:41:05.505
SAILOM

00:41:49.865 --> 00:41:52.145
{\an8}PI DOC

00:42:17.945 --> 00:42:24.505
PI DOC

00:42:49.745 --> 00:42:51.345
I want this one.

00:42:51.425 --> 00:42:53.305
-One of each, right?
-Yes, Ma'am.

00:42:53.385 --> 00:42:55.425
Go wait at the table, dear.
I'll bring them over in a bit.

00:42:55.505 --> 00:42:56.745
Okay!

00:42:59.745 --> 00:43:01.465
Nabnueng!

00:43:01.545 --> 00:43:05.425
-Yes, Mom?
-The clinic's order is almost ready.

00:43:05.505 --> 00:43:06.705
Got it, Mom.

00:43:15.465 --> 00:43:16.665
Mom,

00:43:16.745 --> 00:43:19.225
he’s been staring at his phone

00:43:19.305 --> 00:43:21.745
and moping like this for a week now.

00:43:21.825 --> 00:43:24.265
It’s exactly how he was
when he broke up with Pi Yanin.

00:43:24.345 --> 00:43:25.905
I don't think so, Sweetie.

00:43:25.985 --> 00:43:27.145
Coffee is ready.

00:43:27.225 --> 00:43:28.505
Thank you.

00:43:28.585 --> 00:43:31.945
Nabnueng, your coffee is ready.

00:43:33.065 --> 00:43:34.345
Thank you.

00:43:55.025 --> 00:43:57.385
-Here, I’ll help you.
-Thanks.

00:43:57.465 --> 00:43:58.305
Alright!

00:43:58.385 --> 00:43:59.225
Oof!

00:44:15.225 --> 00:44:16.505
PI DinDin.

00:44:17.225 --> 00:44:18.505
Hey, Lookso.

00:44:18.585 --> 00:44:20.105
Pi Nat,

00:44:20.185 --> 00:44:22.345
I’ve only been gone for a few weeks.

00:44:22.905 --> 00:44:24.145
How did it get so crowded here?

00:44:24.225 --> 00:44:27.465
It’s because PI Nava
Started a TikTok channel

00:44:27.545 --> 00:44:30.145
and features Pi Mickey
and Pi Zoom in the content.

00:44:32.265 --> 00:44:33.905
Wow, that’s cool.

00:44:33.985 --> 00:44:38.745
But with so many customers,
can Sky handle it all by himself?

00:44:38.825 --> 00:44:41.505
Oh, Pi Sky doesn't do the repairs anymore.

00:44:42.145 --> 00:44:47.065
He hired mechanics
and became a dealer instead.

00:44:48.985 --> 00:44:55.025
He says selling parts
is more profitable than fixing them.

00:44:55.105 --> 00:44:58.425
When he’s not meeting clients,

00:44:58.505 --> 00:45:00.785
he helps Pi Nava with wedding shoots.

00:45:01.385 --> 00:45:03.745
And… what about Tawan?

00:45:04.385 --> 00:45:05.505
What’s he doing now?

00:45:05.585 --> 00:45:07.185
Pi Tawan’s--

00:45:07.265 --> 00:45:08.345
DinDin.

00:45:39.145 --> 00:45:40.465
Now, give each other a little kiss.

00:45:42.945 --> 00:45:44.585
-Okay.
-Is the light okay?

00:45:47.425 --> 00:45:48.505
Beautiful.

00:45:49.505 --> 00:45:51.225
Getting tired?

00:45:51.305 --> 00:45:52.825
Not at all, Babe.

00:45:52.905 --> 00:45:53.945
Give me a kiss?

00:45:55.865 --> 00:45:57.745
I hired you guys to work!

00:45:57.825 --> 00:46:00.665
How can you be sweeter than the grooms?

00:46:00.745 --> 00:46:02.505
Get back to shooting!

00:46:02.585 --> 00:46:03.665
Alright then!

00:46:06.345 --> 00:46:07.425
Still at it?

00:46:07.505 --> 00:46:08.865
Alright, alright.

00:46:10.905 --> 00:46:12.785
-How’s the reflector?
-Good enough.

00:46:13.785 --> 00:46:15.665
How much further are you going to walk?

00:46:15.745 --> 00:46:16.865
DinDin!

00:46:23.065 --> 00:46:24.825
Where the hell have you been?

00:46:24.905 --> 00:46:28.825
I called, I texted, and you never replied.
What is wrong with you?

00:46:29.425 --> 00:46:31.625
I went back to being a pilot,
just like you wanted.

00:46:31.705 --> 00:46:34.865
Were you flying in outer space?
Why didn’t you reply?

00:46:35.465 --> 00:46:36.625
I'm sorry.

00:46:37.945 --> 00:46:40.025
I just wanted you to be proud of me,

00:46:41.145 --> 00:46:42.625
as much as I'm proud of you.

00:46:44.905 --> 00:46:47.025
I’ve worked so hard to be a pilot again

00:46:48.705 --> 00:46:50.305
just to ask you to be my boyfriend.

00:46:51.345 --> 00:46:52.385
Wait…

00:46:54.985 --> 00:46:56.385
what did you just say?

00:46:56.465 --> 00:46:57.585
Are you deaf?

00:47:00.945 --> 00:47:02.025
What's it gonna be?

00:47:02.665 --> 00:47:04.145
Will you be my boyfriend?

00:47:07.905 --> 00:47:08.985
Fine.

00:47:09.545 --> 00:47:10.545
I guess I will.

00:47:14.385 --> 00:47:15.945
You look pretty hot in that uniform.

00:47:21.625 --> 00:47:24.345
Let’s find somewhere… to take it off.

00:47:27.425 --> 00:47:29.225
I’ve been wanting to
undress a pilot for a long time.

00:47:30.105 --> 00:47:31.465
Just say you're horny.

00:47:31.545 --> 00:47:32.865
And you're not?

00:47:49.865 --> 00:47:51.505
Pi Doc,

00:47:51.585 --> 00:47:53.225
come swim with me!

00:47:53.305 --> 00:47:55.545
Don't let me be alone!

00:47:56.425 --> 00:47:57.425
Pi Doc!

00:48:00.865 --> 00:48:02.985
You told me to wait…

00:48:06.785 --> 00:48:08.585
and I'm still here, waiting for you.

00:48:50.105 --> 00:48:51.345
Pi Doc Nabnueng!

00:49:01.905 --> 00:49:04.905
I knew I'd find you here!

00:49:30.905 --> 00:49:33.105
Why didn't you answer my calls?

00:49:34.185 --> 00:49:36.265
You didn't answer mine either.

00:49:40.185 --> 00:49:44.425
It’s because of the time zones,
so our schedules never matched.

00:49:45.865 --> 00:49:46.945
Wait a minute.

00:49:47.985 --> 00:49:49.825
Are you doing this…

00:49:50.625 --> 00:49:52.225
to get back at me?

00:49:57.025 --> 00:49:58.985
It was supposed to be a surprise.

00:50:02.585 --> 00:50:06.305
I’ve decided to drop out from the States

00:50:07.545 --> 00:50:09.665
and transfer back to
a university in Thailand.

00:50:09.745 --> 00:50:11.665
Our time will finally be in sync.

00:50:12.905 --> 00:50:14.025
Now,

00:50:15.185 --> 00:50:18.745
you have to answer my video calls.

00:50:18.825 --> 00:50:20.185
No more excuses.

00:50:22.865 --> 00:50:23.985
I will.

00:50:25.625 --> 00:50:28.305
I'll video call you…

00:50:29.585 --> 00:50:31.065
until we're old.

00:50:31.665 --> 00:50:32.625
How's that?

00:50:34.425 --> 00:50:36.145
Is this a proposal?

00:50:37.425 --> 00:50:38.505
Do you want it to be?

00:50:39.425 --> 00:50:40.425
Come.

00:50:40.505 --> 00:50:43.345
Let's go register our marriage right now.

00:50:44.385 --> 00:50:46.425
Whoa… calm down, Pi Doc.

00:50:47.065 --> 00:50:48.505
I'm still a student.

00:50:52.425 --> 00:50:53.705
I missed you so much.

00:51:47.265 --> 00:51:48.305
Pi Doc.

00:51:49.705 --> 00:51:50.945
Yes?

00:51:51.825 --> 00:51:53.665
Do you remember

00:51:53.745 --> 00:51:55.825
the first time you invited me
to go cycling?

00:51:59.065 --> 00:52:00.905
Of course I do. Why?

00:52:03.025 --> 00:52:06.585
Actually, I didn’t like cycling back then.

00:52:07.785 --> 00:52:09.265
I only went

00:52:10.705 --> 00:52:12.025
because of you.

00:52:13.865 --> 00:52:15.145
I already knew that.

00:52:15.225 --> 00:52:16.345
What?

00:52:18.625 --> 00:52:21.345
Your eyes gave it away.

00:52:22.105 --> 00:52:23.665
Admit it.

00:52:30.145 --> 00:52:31.345
What about now?

00:52:31.905 --> 00:52:33.985
Do you like cycling more?

00:52:41.065 --> 00:52:42.425
I love it more than anything.

00:52:50.025 --> 00:52:51.385
But honestly,

00:52:52.785 --> 00:52:54.705
I'd do anything

00:52:55.625 --> 00:52:57.625
as long as I'm with you.

00:52:59.025 --> 00:53:02.585
That's all I ever need.